The paper focuses on developing a motion prediction approach for pedestrians in cluttered environments, which is a common problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also uses neural networks and deep learning techniques to learn human motion behavior, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves modeling human behavior, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on both simulation and real-world datasets, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
